getSequences(List<T>, int) - Static method in class jme.JMEMath
Get all sequences with a specific length
Sample:
* length:2,[1,2] -> [[1,1],[1,2],[2,1],[2,2]]
* length:3,[1] -> [[1,1,1]]
* length:1,[1,2] -> [[1],[2]]
The number of sequences is equal to variations with repetition of m elements taken by n (m^n)
getSequencesNoDuplicates(List<T>, int) - Static method in class jme.JMEMath
Same as getSequences, but 'items' can have duplicates, although duplicate sequences will be erased.
